The paper is about machine comprehension, which involves natural language processing and understanding. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper introduces a new neural network architecture for machine comprehension, which involves deep learning and artificial intelligence, making it also likely to belong to the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training and optimization of the neural network, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of attention mechanisms and bi-directional flow also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), respectively.
